    PREAMBLE
    --------

    The Open Database License (ODbL) is a license agreement intended to 
    allow users to freely share, modify, and use this Database while 
    maintaining this same freedom for others.

    1. DEFINITIONS

    "Database" means a collection of material (the Contents) arranged in a 
    systematic or methodical way and individually accessible by electronic 
    or other means.

    "Derivative Database" means a database based upon the Database, and 
    includes any translation, adaptation, arrangement, modification, or 
    any other alteration of the Database.

    "Contents" means the contents of the Database, which includes the 
    information collected and stored in the Database.

    "Derivative Works" means works based on the Database, such as 
    translations, adaptations, arrangements, modifications, or any other 
    alterations of the Database.

    "Share" means to distribute, transmit, make available, or otherwise 
    share the Database or Derivative Works.

    2. RIGHTS AND OBLIGATIONS

    You are free to:
